      "full_name": "Limited Liability Company “Stan”",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "LLC Stan is a Russian machine-tool manufacturer that produces modern numerical control machines for high-tech industries, including aerospace and defence. The company operates under RT-Capital of the State Corporation Rostec and supplies advanced drilling and milling machines, such as the VMB 55, to enterprises involved in aircraft and engine manufacturing. LLC Stan has provided large machinery to Tupolev PJSC, which produces Tu-160 strategic missile carriers. LLC Stan has signed contracts worth over 14 billion roubles with key defence enterprises, including UEC-Kuznetsov, Uralvagonzavod and Admiralty Shipyards. LLC Stan contributed to the technical re-equipment of the 123rd Aircraft Repair Plant and the Tactical Missile Armament Corporation. Additionally, its machine tools are used in producing PD-8 and PD-14 engines for military aircraft, including the SJ-100 and Be-200 amphibious aircraft. The Be-200 is operated by the 859th Center for the Combat Use of Naval Aviation in Yeysk. LLC Stan is therefore supporting and benefitting from the Government of the Russian Federation, which is responsible for the annexation of Crimea and the destabilisation of Ukraine. LLC Stan is also supporting Russia’s military and industrial complex.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}